Our Approach
 
Our investment approach focuses on key principles to help deliver innovative solutions designed to meet every investment objective.





 
Our Team of Experts
 
Focused on exceptional results, our team of renowned investment professionals are thought leaders with proven track records and global insight.





 
Awards
 
Our vision is to be the top-performing financial services organization in North America. Here are some of our recent accomplishments.











Our History

Our roots date back to before 1925 when Bank of Montreal first provided investment services to institutional clients. More than 85 years later, we are a global firm offering institutional and retail clients a broad array of innovative investment solutions.







Milestones
 
 


2015


2014


2013


2012 - 1925



2015



BMO ETF business leads the Canadian ETF industry in new assets in 2014 for the fourth year in a row (calculations based on Bloomberg data). 


2014


November

BMO Financial Group becomes the first Canadian financial institution to launch ETFs in Hong Kong through BMO Global Asset Management.  


June

BMO Financial Group celebrates five years since its first four ETFs were listed on the TSX on June 4, 2009. 


May

BMO Financial Group acquires F&C Asset Management plc. This acquisition enhances our investment platform capabilities and provides attractive opportunities to leverage ideas cross-border and bring more comprehensive solutions to our clients around the world. 


January

BMO ETF business leads the Canadian ETF industry in new assets for the third year in a row, with over $5 billion in new assets in 2013 (calculations based on Bloomberg data).


2013


March
BMO ETFs surpass $10 billion in assets under management.


January
BMO ETF business leads the Canadian ETF industry in new assets for the second year in a row, with over $5 billion in new assets in 2012 (calculations based on Bloomberg data).


2012 - 1925

 2012 

August

BMO Asset Management Inc. ranks in the top 10 largest fixed income exchange traded product (ETP) providers worldwide by assets under management.  BMO Financial Group announces that its ETF business has surpassed $7 billion in assets under management and has grown by $1 billion in the last two months.



June
BMO Financial Group's ETF business marks its third anniversary by surpassing $6 billion in assets under management.


March
BMO ETFs surpass $5 billion in assets under management in under three years, and in the first two months of 2012 alone, grew by 32 per cent.


February
BMO Asset Management ranks number one in ETF customer loyalty in the Credo Research February 2012 Loyalty Ranking Survey of 33 financial services firms.


January
BMO ETFs reach $4 billion in assets under management.

 2011 

December
BMO ETF business leads the Canadian ETF industry in growth in 2011, accounting for $2.3 billion or 49 per cent of the growth of assets under management (calculations based on Bloomberg data).


September

BMO ETFs reach $3 billion in assets under management in less than two and a half years after the business was launched. BMO Financial Group's ETF business has doubled in 2011 alone.



July
BMO acquires Marshall & Ilsley Corporation (M&I), adding an array of equity, fixed-income and cash management solutions.


April
BMO ETFs reach $2 billion in assets under management in fewer than two years.


January
BMO acquires Hong Kong-based Lloyd George Management and adds more than 20 years of experience in Asian and emerging markets to the firm's offerings.

 2010 

September
BMO Asset Management reaches $1 billion in assets under management only 15 months after entering the ETF market.


July

BMO Investments Inc. launches a new series of four risk-differentiated mutual fund portfolios that invest primarily in ETFs. 



May

BMO Asset Management Inc. is formed in Canada to offer an integrated mix of investment solutions under a single brand name.


 2009 



BMO Financial Group launches its ETF business through BMO Asset Management Inc. (BMO AM), and is the first bank affiliate in Canada to offer its own line up of ETFs. BMO ETFs launches an initial suite of four funds. 


 2008 



BMO is the first major bank to offer Registered Disability Savings Plans.


 2007 



BMO acquires London-based Pyrford International Ltd. and adds more than 25 years of specialized investment firm experience in international equities to its list of capabilities.


 1999 



BMO establishes Monegy, Inc. and adds global high-yield solutions to the fixed-income product offering.


 1974 


BMO launches the First Canadian Mortgage Fund. BMO Mutual Funds is born. 


 1925 


Bank of Montreal begins offering investment services.









